    <!-- Privacy Policy -->
    <h1>KetoNificent Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> July 28, 2023</p>

    <p>At KetoNificent, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use,
        and protect your personal information when you use our drink customization website. By using our website, you
        consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect:</h2>

    <p><strong>1.1 Personal Information:</strong> When you create an account or place an order on our website, we may
        collect personal information such as your name, email address, and phone number.</p>

    <p><strong>1.2 Drink Customization Preferences:</strong> When you use our drink customization features, we may
        collect information about your preferences, such as ingredients, flavors, and special requests.</p>

    <p><strong>1.3 Usage Data:</strong> We may collect non-personal information about how you interact with our website,
        including your IP address, browser type, device information, and pages visited. This information is used to
        analyze website traffic and improve our services.</p>
    <hr>
    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information:</h2>

    <p><strong>2.1 Order Processing:</strong> We use your personal information to process and fulfill your drink orders
        and to communicate with you about your purchases.</p>

    <p><strong>2.2 Account Management:</strong> If you create an account with us, we use your information to manage your
        account, provide customer support, and keep you informed about our products and promotions.</p>

    <p><strong>2.3 Drink Customization:</strong> Your drink customization preferences help us tailor our offerings to
        your tastes and preferences.</p>

    <p><strong>2.4 Analytics:</strong> We may use usage data to analyze website performance, improve user experience,
        and make data-driven business decisions.</p>
    <hr>
    <h2>3. Sharing Your Information:</h2>

    <p><strong>3.1 Third-Party Service Providers:</strong> We may share your personal information with trusted
        third-party service providers who assist us in running our website and delivering orders. These providers are
        obligated to protect your information and only use it for the intended purposes.</p>

    <p><strong>3.2 Legal Requirements:</strong> We may disclose your personal information if required by law, such as in
        response to a court order or government request.</p>
    <hr>
    <h2>4. Data Security:</h2>

    <p><strong>4.1</strong> We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access,
        disclosure, alteration, and destruction.</p>

    <p><strong>4.2</strong> While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your information, no method
        of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee absolute
        data security.</p>
    <hr>
    <h2>5. Your Choices:</h2>

    <p><strong>5.1 Account Control:</strong> You can review and update your account information by logging into your
        account on our website.</p>

    <p><strong>5.2 Marketing Communications:</strong> You have the option to opt-out of receiving marketing
        communications from us. You can do this by following the instructions in our emails or contacting us directly.
    </p>
    <hr>
    <h2>6. Children's Privacy:</h2>

    <p>Our website is designed to be family-friendly and may be used by individuals of all ages, including children
        under the age of 13. However, we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 without
        verifiable parental consent. If you are under 13 years old, please obtain permission from your parent or
        guardian before using our website or providing any personal information to us.</p>

    <p>If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided personal information to us without your
        consent, please contact us using the provided contact information, and we will take appropriate steps to delete
        the information from our records.</p>

    <p>We are committed to complying with all applicable laws and regulations concerning the privacy and protection of
        children's information, including the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA). We encourage parents and
        guardians to be involved in their children's online activities and to help us protect the privacy of their
        children online.</p>
    <hr>
    <h2>7. Changes to the Privacy Policy:</h2>

    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational,
        legal, or regulatory reasons. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting a prominent notice on our
        website or by email.</p>
    <hr>
    <h2>8. Contact Us:</h2>

    <p>If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or our practices, please contact us at:</p>

    <p>KetoNificent<br>
        [Wabash, IN, 46992]<br>
        [loverejoyces@gmail.com]<br>
        [731-616-9394]</p>

    <p>By using our website, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to the
        collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described herein.</p>
</body>
